10. Communities and participation are the core aspects of this new web3 paradigm. That‚Äôs why creating buzz by renting ad spaces on Times Square might highly engage the existing core group of adopters instead of reaching out for new customers.

9. We are experiencing a deep shift in marketing approaches in the web3 era. Tokenomics and other models gaining importance massively in the blockchain ecosystem. Some of them might not work as before but can still create a different kind of value. https://t.co/CP6D9GOCIr

8. Don‚Äôt get me wrong, I‚Äôm ok with it. I love watching NFTs (ideally the one I‚Äôm holding, ofc) appearing on billboards, monitors, everywhere. However, I think this might be creating additional value to the project itself rather than attracting new people. https://t.co/05IQuBAMtn

7. Is it truly a medium for actively gaining interest in an NFT collection, a new de-fi protocol, or just a sophisticated 3.0 flex? Eg. A Cross social post with NFT on Times Squared captioned ‚ÄúProbably nothing‚Äù üôÑ 
Or is it something more, something new?

6. The exposure given by these billboards is great. Yet what I'm thinking is different. Showing your NFTs on Times Square is surely a strong move, but the pictures of it, spread on social media might have a different kind of value.

5. Also, who wouldn‚Äôt want their brand or logo in Times Square?? Exactly, no one with a basic comprehension of marketing strategies. As stated by @TimesSquareNYC, nearly 360k pedestrians enter Times Square, with ads reaching 1.5 million impressions each day https://t.co/QoyKN4408r

4. ‚ÄúHey but being there that must cost a fortune‚Äù. Well yeah, while still not being cheap, renting spaces got more affordable, and relatively smaller brands got to taste the feeling of being up there, among giants such as Coca-Cola, Spotify, and many others.

3. OK, WOW what is this? CONTINUUM by @Krista_Kim, a mesmerizing art performance consisting of an extreme takeover of the whole square for three minutes. The piece was lately auctioned as NFT at @Sothebys  by @steveaoki https://t.co/TKzqSG3r25
